                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/243.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Brown</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Informs Mr. Root that Tegucigalpa was abandoned early yesterday precipitately and
                    occupied last night by the Nicaraguan and revolutionary forces. Also informs Mr.
                    Root that he assumed charge in the interval with aid of consuls to preserve
                    order.</p>
            </div>
